1. A regeneration device comprising:
an absorbent storage unit that stores a portion of an absorbent containing absorbed CO2 or H2S contained in a gas;
a heating unit that heats the absorbent stored in the absorbent storage unit;
an absorbent distribution unit that forms a circulation mechanism that extracts a portion of the absorbent stored in the absorbent storage unit and returns the extracted portion to the absorbent storage unit for distribution;
a water vapor supply unit that generates water vapor from the absorbent that is heated by the heating unit;
an absorbent component recovery unit that is disposed in the absorbent storage unit and brings the absorbent, which is returned to the absorbent storage unit, into countercurrent contact with the water vapor from the water vapor supply unit; and
a dry water vapor supply unit that supplies dry water vapor having a temperature higher than the temperature to which the absorbent in the absorbent storage unit is heated,
wherein a portion of the absorbent stored in the absorbent storage unit is distributed, and a gaseous mass is brought into countercurrent contact with the distributed absorbent.

